title: Two people injured in Valley Springs accident
text: Two people injured in Valley Springs accident Two people injured in Valley Springs accident By Union Democrat staff October 03, 2015 01:00 am Two Valley Springs residents sustained minor injuries in an accident Thursday on Highway 26. About 7 p.m., Jen Giangregorio, 38, of Valley Springs, was driving a 2014 Ford Explorer along Highway 26 and came to a complete stop preparing to turn left onto Saint Andrews Road, according to a California Highway Patrol report. Ray McWilliams, 54, of Valley Springs, was driving a 1998 Dodge Caravan behind Giangregorio and did not notice the Explorer was stopped, the report said. After McWilliam’s Caravan hit the back of Giangregorio’s Explorer, the Explorer was forced into a tree, the report said. Giangregorio was uninjured. McWilliams and his passenger, Kaylee Holler, 9, also of Valley Springs, both sustained minor injuries and were transported to Mark Twain Medical Center in San Andreas. Follow UnionDemocrat.com
